On Wednesday, Islamabad denied violating the ceasefire in Kashmir, a flashpoint for Indian-Pakistani conflicts.
Indian officials accused Pakistan of firing mortars across the border, causing injuries.
The two countries planned to discuss the incident.
India's Prime Minister announced the resumption of a bus service between the divided zones of Kashmir, symbolizing progress after years of conflict.
Despite tensions, Kashmiris on both sides expressed joy at the opportunity to reunite.
Talks between India and Pakistan aimed at peace continue, with hopes for a lasting resolution to the longstanding Kashmir dispute.
